# CODEOWNERS — visibility flag for the secret-handling surface (spec 0068).
#
# The CI workflows inject repository secrets (TMDB_API_KEY, the FIREBASE_* web
# config, FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT) and tools/scripts/inject-mobile-env.mjs is the
# single mechanism that materializes those secrets into a build. A change to
# either is security-relevant and should be reviewed deliberately.
#
# IMPORTANT — this only REQUESTS review, it does not enforce it. CODEOWNERS is a
# hard gate ONLY if branch protection has "Require review from Code Owners"
# enabled on the default branch. On this (solo) repo it currently functions as a
# visibility flag: PRs touching these paths auto-request the owner as reviewer.
# Enabling the branch-protection toggle is the optional other half that turns this
# into a blocking gate.

# CI/CD workflows (secret injection, deploy auth).
/.github/workflows/**            @Versure

# The build-time secret-injection mechanism.
/tools/scripts/inject-mobile-env.mjs   @Versure
